<taxonomicName box="[367,606,1943,1966]" class="Insecta" family="Polymitarcyidae" genus="Tortopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="circumfluus">
<emphasis box="[367,606,1943,1966]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Tortopus circumfluus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, female holotype. 14, fore wing; 15, hind wing (scheme); 16, hind wing, enlarged; 17, abdominal sternum VIII; 18, mesofurcasternal plates.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195435/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" targetBox="[255,1332,207,1019]" targetPageId="13">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1053,1108]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,350,1053,1077]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">FIGURES 19–23.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[356,530,1053,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Polymitarcyidae" genus="Tortopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="harrisi">
<emphasis box="[356,530,1053,1076]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Tortopus harrisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, male holotype: 19, genitalia, v.v. (pa = penial arm); 20–21, details of apex of penes; 22, detail of pedestal and base of forceps, v.v. (k = knob, pd = pedestal, ps = parastylus); 23, female sternum VIII.
